        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 4 at 5:24PM CDT until August 4 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRSJT

The National Weather Service in San Angelo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Crockett County in west central Texas...

* Until 615 PM CDT.

* At 524 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles west of
The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163, or 15 miles south of
Big Lake, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Crockett County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
